Title: DRAFT  CMS Level 1 Calorimeter Trigger Performance Studies  
Author: S. Dasu, J. Lackey, W. H. Smith, W. Temple 
Address: Madison WI 53706  
Affiliation: Department of Physics University of Wisconsin  
Date: December 25, 1994  
Pubnum: CMS TN/94-285  
Abstract: The level-1 calorimeter trigger system for the CMS detector at LHC collider must provide a deadtimeless, pipelined trigger that implements simple algorithms which satisfy the physics efficiency and data rate requirements. In this note we examine the performance of a conceptual design and that of an alternate algorithm for the electron trigger. The algorithms account for energy sharing between neighboring towers and perform hadronic, and optionally, electromagnetic isolation. Through extensive simulation of the level-1 calorimeter trigger, we have determined the background rates and efficiencies for various triggers such as those for electrons, photons, jets and neutrinos.
