Reference-contexts: To simulate the transverse development of the shower, at each 30 cm step three deposits of energy are distributed transversely with a double exponential distribution <ref> [9] </ref>. The parameters in that distribution are scaled to reflect the difference in interaction lengths in the different media. These subdivided deposits of energy at each step are again stored as calorimeter hits. The calorimeter hits are finally summed to provide total energy in each calorimeter tower.
